label.value: microwestern meso-scale quantitative western blot assay

definition.value: A western blot assay that provides a high-throughput, sensitive, and quantitative measurement of proteins from numerous samples via an array of small western blots on a single sheet of nitrocellulose.

label.value: positive/negative ion switching metabolite profiling assay

definition.value: A type of metabolic profiling assay which employs a hybrid dual quadrupole linear ion trap mass spectrometer for steady-state profiling of endogenous polar metabolites from organic extractions from biological samples.
A type of microscopy assay resulting in highly multiplexed immunofluorescence imaging through sequential rounds of imaging followed by fluorophore inactivation.
A type of protein state assay in which antibodies attached to different colored beads and fluorescent reporter dye labels are used in a multiplexed mixture to assay for proteins in specific states.
A specimen that derives from a biofilm that forms on the inner surface of an endotracheal tube while the tube is in the trachea. The specimen is collected upon removal of the tube from the trachea.
A specimen that derives from a biofilm that forms on the inner surface of an endotracheal tube while the tube is in the trachea. The specimen is collected by suction without removing the tube.
The position of the first amino acid in a protein sequence being analyzed (input protein sequence).
The position of the last amino acid in a protein sequence being analyzed (input protein sequence).
The position of the first nucleotide in a gene sequence being analyzed (input gene sequence).
The position of the last nucelotide in a gene sequence being analyzed (input gene sequence).
The position of the first amino acid in a reference protein sequence (sequence being used for comparison).
The position of the last amino acid in a reference protein sequence (sequence being used for comparison).
The position of the first nucleotide in a reference gene sequence (sequence being used for comparison).
The position of the last nucelotide in a reference sequence (sequence being used for comparison).
A length measurement datum between a point at sea or ground level and some point above it.
A Hi-C assay in which a selection step is performed on ligated fragments in order to enrich for ligation products containing specific regions of interest.
An imaging assay in which nuclear magnetic resonance is used to produce information about the interior structure and composition of an input material entity.
An imaging assay that uses a series of X-ray images to produce information about the interior structure and composition of an input material entity.
An imaging assay in which positron-emitting radionuclides are used to visualize functional processes of an input material entity.
A time measurement datum that is the count of collection cycles over which a specimen collection process occurs.
A person or organization that provides material supplies to other people or organizations.

label.value: T cell receptor repertoire sequencing assay

definition.value: A sequencing assay that determines the sequences of DNA or RNA molecules that encode the repertoire of T cell receptors within an input sample.

label.value: B cell receptor repertoire sequencing assay

definition.value: A sequencing assay that determines the sequence of a DNA or RNA molecules that encode the repertoire of B cell receptors within an input sample.
A data item that is the frequency of detection of a specified pathogenic organism in collected specimens.

label.value: prevalence of blood meal specimens from a host organism

definition.value: A data item that is the frequency of blood whose source is from a specified host organism in collected blood meal specimens.

label.value: presence of blood from host organism in blood meal specimen

definition.value: A data item that indicates whether blood in a blood meal specimen came from a specified host organism.
An organism that is the source of a blood meal.
A role borne by an organism that is gained during a process in which another organism ingests blood as food from the organism.
A role of a material entity realized in drawing an arthropod in the direction of the material.

label.value: arthropod collection process with automated identification

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that involves a device that produces data specifying the types of arthropod collected.

label.value: gravid female arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting gravid female arthropods.

label.value: resting flight-capable arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that occurs while an arthropod that is capable of flight is resting outdoors during a period of inactivity.

label.value: daytime arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs in the daytime.

label.value: arthropod resting in human house specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that catches specimens resting inside a human house.
An arthropod specimen collection process that occurs while the arthropods land on a surface.

label.value: flying adult arthropod collection process by passive interception

definition.value: An adult arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting arthropods capable of flight, through the use of a barrier trap.

label.value: device for collection of resting adult arthropods

definition.value: A device that is designed to provide a solid surface that is attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.
A device that is designed for the collection of arthropod larvae or pupae from water and consists of a conical net.

label.value: arthropod trap containing small non-human animal bait

definition.value: An arthropod trap that uses as attractant an animal that is not human and is the size of a chicken or smaller.
An arthropod trap that is designed to trap an arthropod as it emerges from water at the beginning of its adult stage.
An assay that measures ferritin
An assay that measures fibrinogen
An analyte assay that measures the abundance of iron
An analyte assay that measures the abundance of ionized calcium
An analyte assay that measures the abundance of transferrin
An analyte assay that measures the abundance of uric acid
An analyte assay that measures the abundance of globulin
A cytometry assay that measures the abundance and/or characteristics of myelocytes
A cytometry assay that measures the abundance and/or characteristics of metamyelocytes
A cytometry assay that measures the proportion of red blood cells
